project title 
Customer Churn Prediction Project
 Project Description

The **Customer Churn Prediction** project is a Machine Learning classification system designed to predict whether a customer will leave (churn) or continue using a company's services.

In industries like **telecom, banking, and subscription services**, customer retention is very important. Losing customers directly affects revenue. This project helps businesses identify customers who are likely to churn so that preventive actions like offers, discounts, or support improvements can be taken.

The system is built using machine learning algorithms such as **Logistic Regression, Decision Tree, Random Forest, and XGBoost**, and it analyzes customer behavior patterns such as usage, tenure, charges, and service subscription details.

---

## 🎯 Objectives

* To predict whether a customer will churn or not
* To analyze factors affecting customer churn
* To improve customer retention strategies
* To build and compare classification models
* To evaluate model performance using proper metrics

---

## 📊 Dataset Description

The dataset generally contains customer-related information such as:

* Customer ID
* Gender
* Age (if available)
* Tenure (how long customer stayed)
* Monthly Charges
* Total Charges
* Contract type (monthly/yearly)
* Internet Service type
* Payment method
* Additional services (online security, tech support, etc.)
* **Target Variable:** Churn (Yes/No)

You can use datasets from:

* Kaggle Telco Customer Churn Dataset
* IBM Sample Churn Dataset

